name: GEO_BENE_SK
comment: AN INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) ASSIGNED SURROGATE KEY USED TO IDENTIFY A BENEFICIARYS ZIP CODE, AND ESTABLISHES UNIQUENESS OF A CLAIM. THIS IS A COMPONENT OF THE CLAIM 4 AND 5-PART KEYS USED FOR JOINING CLAIMS.

name: CLM_DT_SGNTR_SK
comment: AN INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) ASSIGNED SURROGATE KEY IDENTIFYING A DISTINCT COMBINATION OF RELATED DATES USED TO ESTABLISH UNIQUENESS OF A CLAIM. THE DISTINCT COMBINATION OF DATE GROUPINGS IS A COMPONENT OF THE CLAIM 4 AND 5-PART KEYS.

name: CLM_TYPE_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING THE SOURCE AND TYPE OF CLAIM SUBMITTED THROUGH THE MEDICARE OR MEDICAID PROGRAM.  FOR EXAMPLE:  60 = MEDICARE  NATIONAL CLAIMS HISTORY (NCH) INPATIENT CLAIM   8900 = MEDICAID FEE FOR SERVICE DENTAL     REFERENCE TABLE: CLM_TYPE_CD

name: CLM_NUM_SK
comment: AN INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) ASSIGNED SURROGATE KEY USED TO DIFFERENTIATE CLAIMS THAT HAVE COMMON GEOGRAPHY, CLAIM DATES AND CLAIM TYPES. WHEN THE SAME COMBINATION OF GEO_BENE_SK, CLM_DT_SGNTR_SK, AND CLM_TYPE_CD IS NOT UNIQUE, THE CLM_NUM_SK IS SEQUENCED TO MAKE THE 4 AND 5 PART KEYS UNIQUE.  THIS IS A COMPONENT OF THE CLAIM 4 AND 5-PART KEYS USED FOR JOINING CLAIMS.

name: CLM_LINE_NUM
comment: A NUMBER IDENTIFYING THE POSITION OF THE SERVICE OR ITEM ON THE CLAIM. THIS IS A COMPONENT OF THE 5-PART KEY USED FOR JOINING CLAIMS.

name: CLM_ADDTNL_DCMTN_CD
comment: EFFECTIVE 5/92, INDICATION THAT ADDITIONAL CLAIM-DOCUMENTATION WAS SUBMITTED FOR THIS LINE ITEM SERVICE ON THE NON-INSTITUTIONAL CLAIM.

name: CLM_CLIA_ALERT_IND_CD
comment: EFFECTIVE WITH NCH VERSION G, THE ALERT CODE (RESULTING FROM CLIA EDITING) ADDED BY CWF AS A LINE ITEM ON THE CARRIER CLAIM (NON-DMERC). [NCH]

name: CLM_DMERC_DCSN_IND_SW
comment: EFFECTIVE WITH NCH VERSION G, THE SWITCH IDENTIFYING WHETHER THE DMERC CLAIM REPRESENTS AN ORIGINAL DECISION OR A REVERSAL OF AN EARLIER DECISION ON THE ORIGINAL CLAIM. [NCH]

name: CLM_DUP_CHK_IND_CD
comment: EFFECTIVE 1/1/2004 WITH THE IMPLEMENTATION OF NCH/NMUD CR#1, THE CODE USED TO IDENTIFY AN ITEM OR SERVICE THAT APPEARED TO BE A DUPLICATE BUT HAS BEEN REVIEWED BY A CARRIER AND APPROPRIATELY APPROVED FOR PAYMENT.  NOTE1:  PRIOR TO 10/2005 (IMPLEMENTATION OF NCH/NMUD CR#2), THIS DATA WAS STORED IN POSITION 246 (FILLER) ON THE LINE ITEM TRAILER. [NCH]

name: CLM_ERR_SGNTR_SK
comment: AN IDR ASSIGNED SURROGATE KEY THAT UNIQUELY IDENTIFIES A COMBINATION OF ERRORS THAT HAVE CO-OCCURRED WITHIN SOME SET OF CLAIMS.

name: CLM_FED_TYPE_SRVC_CD
comment: TYPE OF SERVICE AS DEFINED IN THE HCFA MEDICARE CARRIER MANUAL, FOR THIS LINE ITEM ON THE NON-INSTITUTIONAL CLAIM. (NCH)

name: CLM_LINE_CARR_CLNCL_CHRG_AMT
comment: FEE SCHEDULE CHARGE AMOUNT APPLIED FOR THE LINE ITEM CLINICAL LABORATORY SERVICE ON THE CARRIER CLAIM (NON-DMERC).

name: CLM_LINE_CARR_CLNCL_LAB_NUM
comment: THE IDENTIFICATION NUMBER ASSIGNED TO THE CLINICAL LABORATORY PROVIDING SERVICES FOR THE LINE ITEM ON THE CARRIER CLAIM (NON-DMERC).

name: CLM_LINE_CARR_DME_CVRG_BGN_DT
comment: EFFECTIVE 5/92 THROUGH 6/94, THE DATE DURABLE MEDICAL EQUIPMENT (DME) COVERAGE PERIOD STARTED PER CERTIFICATE OF MEDICAL NECESSITY, PRESCRIPTION, OTHER DOCUMENTATION OR CARRIER DETERMINATION.  THIS FIELD IS APPLICABLE TO LINE ITEMS INVOLVING DME, PROSTHETIC, ORTHOTIC AND SUPPLY ITEMS, IMMUNO-SUPPRESSIVE DRUGS, PEN, ESRD AND OXYGEN ITEMS REFERRED TO AS DMEPOS).

name: CLM_LINE_CARR_DME_NCSTY_MO_CNT
comment: EFFECTIVE 5/92 THROUGH 6/94, AS LINE ITEM ON THE CARRIER CLAIM (NON-DMERC), THE COUNT DETERMINED BY THE CARRIER SHOWING THE LENGTH OF NEED (MEDICAL NECESSITY FOR DME IN MONTHS FROM THE START DATE THROUGH THE DETERMINED PERIOD OF NEED. THIS FIELD IS APPLICABLE TO LINE ITEMS INVOLVING DME, PROSTHETIC, ORTHOTIC AND SUPPLY ITEMS, IMMUNO SUPPRESSIVE DRUGS, PEN, ESRD AND OXYGEN ITEMS REFERRED TO AS DMEPOS).    EXCEPTION:  IF THE DME IS DETERMINED TO BE MEDICALLY NECESSARY FOR THE LIFE OF THE BENEFICIARY, 99 IS PLACED IN THIS FIELD, RATHER THAN A MONTH COUNT. [NCH]

name: CLM_LINE_CARR_HPSA_SCRCTY_CD
comment: A CODE USED TO TRACK THE HEALTH PROFESSIONAL SHORTAGE AREA (HPSA) AND PHYSICIAN SCARCITY (PSA) RELATED BONUS PAYMENTS ON PART B PROFESSIONAL CLAIMS.    REFERENCE TABLE: CLM_CARR_HPSA_SCRCTY_CD

name: CLM_LINE_CARR_PSYCH_OT_LMT_AMT
comment: FOR TYPE OF SERVICE PSYCHIATRIC, OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY OR PHYSICAL THERAPY, THE AMOUNT OF ALLOWED CHARGES APPLIED TOWARD THE LIMIT CAP FOR THIS LINE ITEM SERVICE ON THE NONINSTITUTIONAL CLAIM. [NCH]

name: CLM_LINE_DMERC_HCPCS_CD_TXT
comment: PRIOR TO NCH VERSION H THIS FIELD WAS NAMED: CWFB_DME_ITM_NOC_HCPCS_CD_TXT. [NCH]

name: CLM_LINE_DMERC_SCRN_SVGS_AMT
comment: PRIOR TO NCH VERSION H THIS FIELD WAS NAMED: CWFB_DME_SCRN_SVGS_AMT AND THE FIELD SIZE WAS S9(5)V99. [NCH]

name: CLM_LINE_HCT_HGB_TYPE_CD
comment: EFFECTIVE SEPTEMBER 1, 2008 WITH THE IMPLEMENTATION OF NCH CR#3, THE CODE USED TO IDENTIFY WHICH READING IS REFLECTED IN THE HEMATOCRIT/HEMOGLOBIN RESULT NUMBER FIELD ON THE NONINSTITUTIONAL CLAIM. [NCH]

name: CLM_LINE_HCT_HGB_RSLT_NUM
comment: EFFECTIVE SEPTEMBER 1, 2008, WITH THE IMPLEMENTATION OF NCH CR#3, THE NUMBER USED TO IDENTIFY THE MOST RECENT HEMATOCRIT OR HEMOGLOBIN READING ON THE NONINSTITUTIONAL CLAIM.  NOTE:  THE HEMATOCRIT/HEMOGLOBIN TEST RESULT FIELD IS A REDEFINED FIELD.  THE FIELD IS BEING DEFINED AS X(3) AND REDEFINED AS NUMERIC (99V9).  A NUMERIC TEST ON THE ALPHANUMERIC FIELD IS NEEDED.  WHENEVER A USER WANTS TO USE THE FIELD THEY MUST TEST THE ALPHANUMERIC FIELD FOR NUMERICS AND IF IT IS NUMERIC THEN THE 99V9 DEFINITION WOULD BE USED.  THE OLDER DATA WILL CAUSE AN ABEND IF TRYING TO PROCESS NUMERIC DATA WITH CHARACTERS. [NCH]

name: CLM_LINE_PRFNL_DME_PRICE_AMT
comment: EFFECTIVE 5/92, THE AMOUNT REPRESENTING THE LOWER OF FEE SCHEDULE FOR PURCHASE OF NEW OR USED DME, OR ACTUAL CHARGE.  IN CASE OF RENTAL DME, THIS AMOUNT REPRESENTS THE PURCHASE CAP; RENTAL PAYMENTS CAN ONLY BE MADE UNTIL THE CAP IS MET.  THIS LINE ITEM FIELD IS APPLICABLE TO NON-INSTITUTIONAL CLAIMS INVOLVING DME, PROSTHETIC, ORTHOTIC AND SUPPLY ITEMS, IMMUNOSUPPRESSIVE DRUGS, PEN, ESRD AND OXYGEN ITEMS REFERRED TO AS DMEPOS. [NCH]

name: CLM_LINE_PRFNL_INTRST_AMT
comment: AMOUNT OF INTEREST TO BE PAID FOR THIS LINE ITEM SERVICE ON THE NON-INSTITUTIONAL CLAIM.  **NOTE: THIS IS NOT INCLUDED IN THE LINE ITEM NCH PAYMENT (REIMBURSEMENT) AMOUNT.

name: CLM_LINE_PRFNL_PNLTY_AMT
comment: EFFECTIVE WITH NCH VERSION H, THE 10% PAYMENT REDUCTION AMOUNT (APPLICABLE TO A LATE FILING CLAIM) FOR THE LINE ITEM SERVICE ON THE NONINSTITUTIONAL CLAIM. [NCH]

name: CLM_MR_SCRN_RSLT_IND_CD
comment: EFFECTIVE WITH NCH VERSION G, CODE INDICATING THE OUTCOME OF THE MEDICAL REVIEW (MR) UNITS EVALUATION OF THE DMERC LINE ITEM. [NCH]

name: CLM_MR_SCRN_SUSPNSN_CD
comment: EFFECTIVE WITH VERSION G, THE  MEDICAL REVIEW (MR) SCREEN THAT CAUSED  DMERC LINE ITEM TO SUSPEND.

name: CLM_MTUS_IND_CD
comment: 1) CODE INDICATING THE UNITS ASSOCIATED WITH SERVICES NEEDING UNIT REPORTING ON THE LINE ITEM FOR THE CARRIER CLAIM (NON-DMERC). [NCH]    2) PRIOR TO VERSION H THIS FIELD WAS NAMED: CWFB_DME_MTUS_IND_CD. [NCH]

name: CLM_PHYSN_ASTNT_CD
comment: EFFECTIVE 1/92, IDENTIFICATION OF CLAIMS THAT HAVE BEEN PAID A REDUCED FEE SCHEDULE AMOUNT (65%, 75% OR 85%) BECAUSE A PHYSICIANS ASSISTANT PERFORMED THE SERVICES.

name: CLM_PMT_80_100_CD
comment: THE CODE INDICATING THAT THE AMOUNT SHOWN IN THE PAYMENT FIELD ON THE NON-INSTITUTIONAL LINE ITEM REPRESENTS EITHER 80% OR 100% OF THE ALLOWED CHARGES LESS ANY DEDUCTIBLE, OR 100% LIMITATION OF LIABILITY ONLY.

name: CLM_PMT_IND_CD
comment: THE PAYMENT SCREEN USED TO DETERMINE THE ALLOWED CHARGE FOR THE LINE ITEM SERVICE ON THE NON-INSTITUTIONAL CLAIM.

name: CLM_PRCNG_LCLTY_CD
comment: CODE DENOTING THE CARRIER-SPECIFIC LOCALITY USED FOR PRICING THE SERVICE FOR THIS LINE ITEM ON THE CARRIER CLAIM (NON-DMERC). [NCH]

name: GEO_PRCNG_SK
comment: AN INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) ASSIGNED NUMERIC SURROGATE KEY IDENTIFYING A PARTICULAR GEOGRAPHICAL LOCATION BY ITS FIVE-DIGIT ZIP CODE.

name: GEO_PRCNG_ZIP4_CD
comment: A FOUR DIGIT EXTENSION TO A ZIP CODE THAT REPRESENTS A SUBDIVISION FOR MAILING PURPOSES OF THE ZIP CODE.

name: CLM_PRCSG_IND_CD
comment: THE CODE INDICATING THE REASON A LINE ITEM ON THE NONINSTITUTIONAL CLAIM WAS ALLOWED OR DENIED.  NOTE2:  EFFECTIVE 4/1/02, THIS FIELD WAS EXPANDED TO TWO BYTES TO ACCOMMODATE NEW VALUES. THE NCH NEARLINE FILE DID NOT EXPAND THE CURRENT 1-BYTE FIELD BUT INSTITUTED A CROSSWALK OF THE 2-BYTE FIELD TO THE 1-BYTE CHARACTER VALUE. SEE TABLE OF CODE FOR THE CROSSWALK. [NCH]

name: CLM_PRMRY_PYR_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING THE COVERAGE TYPE OF THE PRIMARY PAYER WHEN MEDICARE IS THE SECONDARY PAYER AT THE CLAIM LINE AS DEFINED BY THE COMMON WORKING FILE (CWF).    REFERENCE TABLE: CLM_PRMRY_PYR_CD

name: CLM_PRVDR_SPCLTY_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING THE CENTERS FOR MEDICARE AND MEDICAID SERVICES (CMS) SPECIALTY OF A PROVIDER OR SUPPLIER.  FOR EXAMPLE:  11 = INTERNAL MEDICINE  49 = AMBULATORY SURGICAL CENTER    REFERENCE TABLE: CLM_PRVDR_SPCLTY_CD

name: CLM_SUPLR_TYPE_CD
comment: THE TYPE OF SUPPLIER.

name: CLM_TYPE_SRVC_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING THE TYPE OF SERVICE DESIGNATED TO A SPECIFIC HEALTHCARE COMMON PROCEDURE CODING SYSTEM (HCPCS) CODE SUBMITTED ON PROFESSIONAL CLAIMS.

name: CLM_WVR_PRVDR_LBLTY_SW
comment: EFFECTIVE WITH NCH VERSION G, THE SWITCH INDICATING THE BENEFICIARY WAS NOTIFIED THAT THE ITEM, REPORTED AS A DMERC LINE ITEM, MAY NOT BE CONSIDERED MEDICALLY NECESSARY AND HAS AGREED IN WRITING TO PAY FOR THE ITEM. [NCH]

name: CLM_SRC_ID
comment: AN IDENTIFIER INDICATING WHERE THE SOURCE OF THE CLAIM DATA IN THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) ORIGINATED FROM.   VALID VALUES:  20000 = NATIONAL CLAIMS HISTORY (NCH)  21000 = FISCAL INTERMEDIARY SHARED SYSTEM (FISS)  22000 = MULTI-CARRIER SYSTEM (MCS)  23000 = VIABLE INFORMATION PROCESSING SYSTEMS (VIPS) MEDICARE SYSTEM (VMS)  24000 = ENCOUNTER DATA PROCESSING SYSTEM (EDPS)  25000 = ENCOUNTER MEDICAID DUALS 837 CLAIMS  AND DUALS MEDICAID DRUG CLAIMS (DMDC)  N/A = MEDICAID

name: GEO_DROP_OFF_SK
comment: AN IDR ASSIGNED SURROGATE KEY USED TO IDENTIFY A BENEFICIARYS LOCALE.

name: GEO_DROP_OFF_ZIP4_CD
comment: A FOUR-DIGIT ZIP CODE EXTENSION DEFINED BY THE UNITED STATES POSTAL SERVICE (USPS) IDENTIFYING A SPECIFIC AMBULANCE DROP-OFF LOCATION.    REFERENCE TABLE: GEO_ZIP9_CD

name: GEO_PTNT_PCKP_SK
comment: AN INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) ASSIGNED NUMERIC SURROGATE KEY IDENTIFYING A PARTICULAR GEOGRAPHICAL LOCATION BY ITS FIVE-DIGIT ZIP CODE.

name: GEO_PTNT_PCKP_ZIP4_CD
comment: IDENTIFIES THE POINT OF PICKUP ZIP CODE EXTENSION ON CARRIER CLAIMS.  THE POINT OF PICKUP ZIP CODE IS USED FOR PRICING AMBULANCE SERVICES.(NCH)

name: CLM_LINE_PRFNL_MTUS_CNT
comment: (1) THE COUNT OF THE TOTAL UNITS ASSOCIATED WITH SERVICES NEEDING UNIT REPORTING SUCH AS TRANSPORTATION, MILES, ANESTHESIA TIME UNITS, NUMBER OF SERVICES, VOLUME OF OXYGEN OR BLOOD UNITS.  THIS IS A LINE ITEM FIELD ON THE CARRIER CLAIM (NON-DMERC) AND IS USED FOR BOTH ALLOWED AND DENIED SERVICES.  NOTE:  FOR ANESTHESIA (MTUS INDICATOR = 2) THIS FIELD SHOULD BE REPORTED IN TIME UNIT INTERVALS, I.E. 15 MINUTE INTERALS OR FRACTION THEREOF. IT APPEARS THAT SOME CARRIERS ARE REPORTING MINUTES INSTEAD OF TIME UNITS.[NCH]  (2) EFFECTIVE WITH NCH VERSION G, THE COUNT OF THE TOTAL UNITS ASSOCIATED WITH THE DMERC LINE ITEM SERVICE NEEDING UNIT REPORTING, INCLUDING NUMBER OF SERVICES, VOLUME OF OXYGEN AND DRUG DOSE. [NCH]

name: CLM_LCL_PMT_80_100_CD
comment: A CODE INDICATING WHETHER A CLAIM LINE SERVICE IS PAYABLE AT 80%.

name: CLM_LCL_SRVC_DDCTBL_SW
comment: A SWITCH INDICATING WHETHER A CLAIM LINE SERVICE IS SUBJECT TO A DEDUCTIBLE.

name: CLM_SRVC_DDCTBL_SW
comment: A VALUE IDENTIFYING WHETHER A SERVICE LINE IS SUBJECT TO THE DEDUCTIBLE.    REFERENCE TABLE: CLM_SRVC_DDCTBL_SW

name: CLM_LINE_PRCNG_ZIP5_CD
comment: DMERC LINE PRICING ZIP CODE

name: CLM_BENE_PRMRY_PYR_PD_AMT
comment: LINE BENEFICIARY PRIMARY PAYER PAID AMOUNT

name: CLM_MDCR_PRMRY_PYR_ALOWD_AMT
comment: LINE PRIMARY PAYER ALLOWED CHARGE AMOUNT

name: CLM_PTNT_PCKP_ZIP5_CD
comment: IDENTIFIES THE SUBMITTED POINT OF PICKUP/PLACE OF SERVICE 5 DIGIT ZIP CODE ON CARRIER CLAIMS.  THE ZIP CODE IS USED FOR PRICING SERVICES.

name: CLM_DROP_OFF_ZIP5_CD
comment: IDENTIFIES THE SUBMITTED POINT OF DROP OFF 5 DIGIT ZIP CODE ON AMBULANCE CLAIMS.

name: CLM_POS_PHYSN_ORG_NAME
comment: THE NAME OF THE POS PHYSICIAN/ORGANIZATION

name: CLM_POS_PRVDR_1ST_LINE_ADR
comment: THE POS PROVIDERS LINE 1 ADDRESS

name: CLM_POS_PRVDR_1ST_NAME
comment: THE FIRST NAME OF THE POS PROVIDER.

name: CLM_POS_PRVDR_2ND_LINE_ADR
comment: THE POS PROVIDERS LINE 2 ADDRESS.

name: CLM_POS_PRVDR_CITY_NAME
comment: THE CITY NAME ASSOCIATED WITH THE POS PROVIDERS ADDRESS.

name: CLM_POS_PRVDR_MDL_NAME
comment: THE MIDDLE NAME OF THE POS PROVIDER

name: CLM_POS_PRVDR_USPS_STATE_CD
comment: THE USPS STATE CODE ASSOCIATED WITH THE POS PROVIDERS ADDRESS.

name: CLM_POS_PRVDR_ZIP5_CD
comment: THE US POSTAL SERVICE CODE THAT IS ASSOCIATED WITH A GEOGRAPHICAL AREA.

name: CLM_POS_PRVDR_ZIP4_CD
comment: A FOUR DIGIT EXTENSION TO A ZIP CODE THAT REPRESENTS A SUBDIVISION FOR MAILING PURPOSES OF THE ZIP CODE

name: CLM_RNDRNG_NPI_IN_BLG_GRP_SW
comment: THE FIELD USED TO IDENTIFY IF THE RENDERING PROVIDER NPI IS A MEMBER OF THE GROUP PRACTICE BILLING NATIONAL PROVIDER IDENTIFIER (NPI).

name: CLM_LINE_CBA_CD
comment: THE CODE USED TO IDENTIFY THE COMPETITIVE BID AREA (CBA).

name: CLM_LINE_CBA_BGN_DT
comment: THE BEGINNING DATE FOR A PARTICULAR ROUND OF COMPETITIVE BIDDING USED TO DETERMINE THE ELIGIBILITY FOR CONTRACT OR GRANDFATHERING SUPPLIERS.

name: CLM_LINE_CLIA_NUM
comment: THE CLIA CERTIFICATE OF WAIVER OR THE CLINICAL LABORATORY IMPROVEMENT AMENDMENT (CLIA) CERTIFICATE OF REGISTRATION IDENTIFICATION NUMBER ASSIGNED TO THE LABORATORY TESTING SITE THAT RENDERED THE SERVICES ON THIS CLAIM.

name: CLM_LINE_RFRG_CLIA_FAC_ID
comment: REFERRING CLINICAL LABORATORY IMPROVEMENT AMENDMENT (CLIA) FACILITY IDENTIFICATION.

name: CLM_LINE_FAC_FDA_MQSA_NUM
comment: THE MAMMOGRAPHY QUALITY STANDARDS ACT (MQSA) PROVIDES SPECIFIC STANDARDS REGARDING THOSE QUALIFIED TO PERFORM SCREENING AND DIAGNOSTIC MAMMOGRAMS AND HOW THEY SHOULD BE CERTIFIED. FACILITIES THAT PROVIDE MAMMOGRAPHY SERVICES MUST MEET NATIONAL QUALITY STANDARDS. THE CERTIFICATE IS ISSUED BY THE FOOD AND DRUG ADMINISTRATION (FDA).

name: CLM_FRGN_ADR_CD
comment: A CODE SIGNIFYING THE BENEFICIARY HAS A PERMANENT ADDRESS OUTSIDE OF THE UNITED STATES (U.S.) AND PURCHASED DURABLE MEDICAL EQUIPMENT, PROSTHETICS, ORTHOTICS, AND SUPPLIES (DMEPOS) WHICH WERE FURNISHED IN THE U.S.    VALID VALUE:  EX = EXPATRIATE BENEFICIARY

name: META_SK
comment: A UNIQUE LEGACY NUMERIC VALUE ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR), FORMULATED WITH A DATE AND A 3-DIGIT SEQUENCE NUMBER, WHICH IDENTIFIES THE BATCH PROCESS THAT INITIALLY LOADED A ROW IN THE IDR. DUE TO THE LIMITATION OF A 3-DIGIT VALUE, THIS IS BEING REPLACED BY META_SRC_PRCSG_ID ON NEW IDR TABLES AS THE SOURCE DATA TRACKING STANDARD.

name: META_SRC_SK
comment: A UNIQUE NUMERIC VALUE ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) USED TO IDENTIFY THE SPECIFIC SOURCE OF THE DATA WHEN A ROW IS LOADED INTO THE IDR.    REFERENCE TABLE: V2_MDCR_META_DCTNRY_SRC

name: META_LST_UPDT_SK
comment: AN IDR ASSIGNED SURROGATE KEY USED TO IDENTIFY THE BATCH PROCESS THAT LOADED OR LAST UPDATED A ROW, WHICHEVER OCCURRED LAST.

name: META_LST_UPDT_SRC_SK
comment: A UNIQUE NUMERIC VALUE ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) USED TO IDENTIFY THE SPECIFIC SOURCE OF THE DATA WHEN A ROW IS LOADED INTO THE IDR.    REFERENCE TABLE: V2_MDCR_META_DCTNRY_SRC

name: META_SRC_PRCSG_ID
comment: A VALUE ASSIGNED BASED ON A BATCH IDENTIFICATION IN ORDER TO TRACE IT BACK TO ITS ORIGINAL SOURCE. IT WILL ONLY BE POPULATED WHEN A RECORD IS INSERTED.

name: META_LTST_SRC_PRCSG_ID
comment: A VALUE ASSIGNED BASED ON A BATCH IDENTIFICATION IN ORDER TO TRACE IT BACK TO ITS ORIGINAL SOURCE. IT WILL ONLY BE POPULATED WHEN A RECORD IS SUBSEQUENTLY UPDATED.

name: IDR_INSRT_TS
comment: THE SYSTEM DATE AND TIME ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) WHILE PERFORMING AN INSERT OPERATION.

name: IDR_UPDT_TS
comment: THE SYSTEM DATE AND TIME ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) WHEN UPDATES ARE MADE TO ANY NON-PRIMARY KEY COLUMN.
